6:
I-I am no r-rabbit! I'm the
CHAMPIOOON!
9: Oh, and quite a valiant one at that!
11:
Is that so? Do your best to protect
Stella now, little Champion.
13:
I have an idea! Perhaps you're
looking for a sword in your... size?
Come to my shop and we'll find
something perfect for you!
25:
Heh. Do not worry, Stella. Compared
to dealing with nobles at the palace,
this is nothing.
27:
I am more embarrassed than
anything. Repeating old, familiar
lines should be easy enough, but
now... In this form...
35: You say that, but the truth is...
38:
...Never mind. As long as you feel
that way, Stella, I appreciate it.
Thank you.
48:
What do you think? Does anyone
you spoke to seem...
51:
...Perhaps not deceitful, but... Is there
someone you think is hiding their
true intentions?
60:
Ah, I believe his name was Glaives...
He made his fortune dealing with
adventurers, though it seems he
recently began offering insurance,
as well.
62:
He was boasting about having
journeyed together with the
Tempest and the Celestial Blitz, but—
65:
That much, at least, seems to be
true.
67:
I have confirmed a few things about
him. For one, his business is
legitimate. He also appears to have
a past with Leon and company.
69:
Indeed. Though he looks to have put
adventuring behind him.
72:
In which case, he should hardly be
cause for concern.
75:
F-Father... This is terrible! It's Hasta...
H-he's gone!
77:
You brought your boy here? Surely
he's just lost somewhere... right?
79:
W-well, actually... You see... We've
been receiving threatening letters
for the past few days—
82:
Suizen, gather what news you can
from your ninjas and protect Stella.
104: What the... Is that... a talking rabbit?
107:
Hey, mister! I got so turned around, I
have no idea where I am! C-could
you te—
110:
C-cram it, fuzzball! Don't you take
another step!
126:
Indeed, a bunny I may be... But just
you wait. In just a moment I shall
free you fro— Hnngh. Grr! This lock is
so small...
129:
Mr. Bunny... Is my grandpa... a bad
person?
131:
That man said so... He said my
grandpa's no good...
134:
...Focus on escaping for now. We can
talk later—
137:
Plannin' to rush off without so much
as a goodbye? Can't have that now,
can we, Hasta?
140:
Shall I assume your grudge is with
Glaives and his organization?
143:
Is this something to do with the
insurance? Or... perhaps you have a
problem with his moneylending
business, instead?
146:
Well, lookit the brains on this pile of
fluff! Glaive's gotten rich from dirty
schemes for long enough. We're
gonna take that money off his
hands.
151:
Insurance is meant to be a safety
net to protect adventurers. And
while I dislike moneylending, you
cannot blame a businessman for
making money.
154:
...All you seek is violence... and an
easy target for it.
157:
Oh yeah? And what're YOU gonna
do about it?
160:
Hasta. At my signal, run—get to the
exit, no matter what.
164:
Trust in me, Hasta! I shall see you
safely home!
167:
Hahaha! Big talk for an overgrown
rat. We'll s—
183:
Think you'll get away with this, y'little
mongrel?! You have no IDEA how
many of us there are! We'll get that
brat back in no time!
186:
Indeed... It would seem you and I are
alike, in that way...
193:
You are not the only ones with
friends...
202:
Now, now. Is it really THAT surprising
that I'd come to save you, muffin?
206:
A wondrous surprise that you were
able to tear yourself away from
viewing Stella in her finery.
209:
...I jest, of course. You have my
sincere thanks, Belsidia.
216:
You were rather captivating
yourself, playing the lost little rabbit...
220:
Y-you saw that? Why would you
wait so long to help out?!
